description.0: Hercules and Thor try to solve the mystery of the "spontaneous insanity" afflicting New York. But Herc's hunting for answers lands him in deep trouble!
description.1: Dracula seeks out the Chimera statue, an ancient relic imbued with energy of the Cosmic Eternal.
description.2: Captured...by MAHKIZMO! Reed, Johnny, and Ben have become prisoners of the dreaded despot in his future realm of Machus! Only Medusa is free, and it's up to her to take on an entire world of masculine monsters to set the FF free!
description.4: Man-Wolf steps out in the moonlight to take on the deranged Kraven the Hunter! Jameson's at risk of having his head mounted on Kravinoff's wall!
description.8: While holding a pity party for himself, Richard Rory encounters a young woman who's at the center of a kidnapping plot. Man-Thing provides an assist against the Demons of Liberation.
description.11: The first appearance of Wolverine!  And he throws down in one of Marvel's greatest battles with the Incredible Hulk!
description.12: Spider-Man squares off against the HULK! Hulk is always mad, but why is he staging a prison break? And can Peter find out the reason before he gets SMASHED?
description.17: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 7: T'Challa enters Killmonger's lair, but is quickly accosted and left for dead by Sombre. Contains only "Blood Stains on Virgin Snow!"
description.19: The Man-Thing proves a silent stalker when he helps Daredevil take out Gladiator. The full barrage of Death-Stalker's powers incapacitates both Man-Thing and Hornhead!
description.26: When the Defenders are lured to hell, they'll enlist the aid of the Son of Satan to free themselves!
description.27: Alpha the Ultimate Mutant is Magneto's newest creation. Are the Defenders powerful enough to defeat Alpha, Magneto and the Brotherhood?
description.31: Death personified is on the heels of an entire battalion of men…and Marine Corps Sergeant John Kowalski is most at risk!
description.37: Man-Thing restores harmony to a married couple after thwarting a demonic presence in their swamp.
description.39: Green Goblin attacks a truck carrying radioactive materials. What is the villain's end goal with this dangerous bounty? Plus, Peter's friends and family rally to MJ's side after she is injured by an explosive. Green Goblin makes Spider-Man choose between saving his friends, or Aunt May!
description.40: Following the attack on the Inhuman wedding, the Avengers and Fantastic Four return from the Hidden Land. The Scarlet Witch agrees to continue her hex training with Agatha Harkness, due to her winnowing control over her abilities. While Wanda and Agatha battle Necrodamus, Mantis makes her move on Vision.
description.41: Perhaps the most action-packed Cap thriller of them all! Read, as the world ask, "Where is Captain America!"
description.42: Guest-starring Blade! The vampire hunter is primed and ready to take down Morbius!
description.44: Just as Ghost Rider stops the One Man Zodiac, Satan himself puts in a bid for the soul of Johnny Blaze! Roxanne is tormented by hellish visions of her father.
description.45: While in Canada, Hulk is lured into an occult ritual conducted by Marie Cartier. Will Marie use Hulk's body as the host for an evil spirit?
description.46: Who was Ego before he was a Living Planet? Thor enters the dark recesses of Ego's mind...and surely wishes he hadn't.
description.47: A woman believes her husband was killed by a supernatural being...and asks private investigator Hannibal King to take the case!
description.48: Morbius sinks his teeth into yet another victim! But he may have feeder's remorse after this morsel!
description.49: Johnny and Ben's day of shopping is cut short when they notice the Baxter Building is being invaded in its vacancy. Meanwhile, the Nuclear Man demands the whereabouts of Thundra. But for what purpose?
description.51: Matt Murdock investigates the disappearance of Professor Ted Sallis, and gains intel on the Floridian swamp creature known as the Man-Thing.
description.59: Professor Xavier sends a plea for help to the Defenders to stop Magneto and his Brotherhood of Evil Mutants!
description.60: Bruce winds up in the Appalachian Mountains where he meets Lincoln, a radioactive monstrosity. And Lincoln's radioactivity is killing the rest of his town!
description.61: Iron Man's epic battle with the Mandarin continues! If he's got any chance of winning he's going to have to make the unlikeliest alliance yet! Sunfire and the Golden Avenger against the Mandarin! Ultimo lives, but will our heroes!
description.62: Thor finds unlikely allies in Galactus and Firelord. With the combined might of these two, will Thor and Herc be able to neutralize Ego, the Living Planet?
description.63: Showgirls in danger! Dracula's been stalking the streets of London, keen for new prey. Will Blade, Vampire Hunter, answer the call of the night? And if Blade should fail in saving Trudy, what disastrous consequences will ensue?
description.64: The bells stop chiming when an uninvited guest crashes the wedding of Quicksilver and Crystal. The Fantastic Four and the Inhuman Royal Family must spring into action to save the nuptials without having their minds wiped! Will another unexpected guest save the bride's big day?
description.67: John Jameson sees the impact his debilitating condition has on his life. Meanwhile, NASA comes to collect their AWOL astronaut!
description.71: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 6: T'Challa sets out for N'Jadaka to solve the mystery of Zatama's murder.
description.73: The return of Green Goblin! After a fulfilling Sunday together, Peter and MJ decide to spend a quiet evening at his and Harry's apartment. But as Peter opens the door, an explosion is set off! Who has rigged Peter's apartment? And is his secret identity as Spider-Man a secret no longer?
description.74: It's a surprise wedding issue! The Avengers' dinner is interrupted by Gorgon, member of the Inhuman royal family, who extends an invite to the wedding of Quicksilver and Crystal! However, the Avengers were kept unaware of the wedding! The team drops everything and transports to watch their fellow Avenger be wed in holy Inhuman matrimony. But, will the wedding go off without a sneak attack?
description.75: Captain America is no more, and the Falcon must face the raw power of Lucifer! Will this be Sam Wilson's finest hour? Or will this be his day of doom? Find out now as the Falcon stand alone!
description.76: Captain Marvel stops the Lunatic Legion's Nitro from getting away with Compound 13 nerve gas!
description.78: El Tigre undergoes a strange mutation!
description.79: Man-Thing inadvertently causes distress to an elderly woman living deep in the swamps. Later, the swamp monster comes to the rescue of the woman's husband, embroiling himself in the couple's lives.
description.82: Dracula runs amok throughout the streets of London! Who will be his next victim?
description.87: Hulk is reverted back to Bruce Banner by an act of brute force. Banner can only watch in horror as the Counter-Earth battle rages on in D.C. Who is the madman posturing as President of Counter-Earth? And will Hulk be able to save his friend Adam Warlock from certain execution?
description.89: Nuklo, the son of Whizzer and Miss America, has escaped the confines of the Chrono Module! Scarlet Witch makes a shocking discovery about her and Quicksilver's parentage.
description.92: With the Avengers and Fantastic Four stuck in a predicament that could threaten the entire city, and Daredevil guarded by a brainwashed Black Widow, Mandrill is able to carry out his plans and take over the White House!
description.93: The entire ""Zodiac"" crew is revealed to be a single mercenary! Stuntmaster pitches in to help Ghost Rider against this sinister threat.
description.94: Presenting: The raw, pulsating power of the great Golden Avenger! Iron Man's mightiest foes strike: Mandarin, Unicorn, Sunfire, and the mysterious Yellow Claw! This is it! The story we had to call confrontation!
description.95: Chaos seizes Midgard as New York prepares for the coming of Galactus. But is this all an empty threat? Thor prepares to do battle with Ego.
description.96: The Lord of Vampires continues his journey through horror! The spirits of Dunwick Castle are restless, and have been terrorizing the surrounding populace!
description.97: Meet Lilith, the DAUGHTER OF DRACULA!
description.98: The Sub-Mariner has declared war on the surface world as vengeance for what Mister Fantastic has done to Sue and Franklin. The Fantastic Four springs into action to fight Namor and his band of sea monsters! With the help of Thundra, can the FF protect the shore and its inhabitants while attempting to save the marriage of Reed and Sue?
description.99: Spider-Man finds himself in a shoot-out with Tarantula and Punisher after saving a cruise ship from hijacking. Plus, Peter's friends grow suspicious about his double identity, and Harry Osborn discovers Peter's spider suit!

5.text: Ka-Zar helps a man who's obsessed with slaying a beast from the sea!

6.text: After a century on ice, the Monster thaws and awakens! A modern world emerges, promising new terrors and torments. But will Frankenstein’s Monster reel it in when he meets Night-Creature?

7.text: When the family of the late F. A. Schist travels to Florida to find the remains of their father, they are shocked to discover the MAN-THING instead!

8.text: While holding a pity party for himself, Richard Rory encounters a young woman who's at the center of a kidnapping plot. Man-Thing provides an assist against the Demons of Liberation.

9.text: The battle between the Werewolf and Atlas makes its way to the famed Chinese Theater, where Buck comes to his beastly friend’s rescue!

11.text: What would the comic book landscape look like without Wolverine? It'd be sad and dreary place. Thankfully, Logan made his debut in this issue.

13.text: The Fantastic Four battle around the world against the Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse!

14.text: Learn the tragic origin of Man’s Last Hope…Jonathan Raven! The Death Breeders are deployed against Killraven and Carmilla Frost!

15.text: Six Fists of Fury! The Sons of the Tiger are back in action in “The Way of the Jackal!”

16.text: While eating at a Chinese restaurant, Shang-Chi is nearly killed by murderous waiters! But that's the least of his problems -- Sir Denis and Black Jack Tarr are still in captivity, and Fu Manchu wants to destroy Mount Rushmore!

17.text: Contains only "Blood Stains on Virgin Snow!" story. PANTHER’S RAGE PART 7: T’Challa enters Killmonger’s lair, but is quickly accosted and left for dead by Sombre.

19.text: The Man-Thing proves a silent stalker when he helps Daredevil take out Gladiator. The full barrage of Death-Stalker's powers incapacitates both Man-Thing and Hornhead!

20.text: Iron Fist confronts Harold Meachum, coming face-to-face with the shadowy man who wants him dead. The Ninja pulls out some incredible moves in battle with Triple-Iron. Harold’s daughter Joy Meachum has an unfortunate misunderstanding with Iron Fist. The only word on her lips? “Revenge!”

23.text: Can the Sorcerer Supreme defeat Death? The Ancient One blesses Strange with a thoughtful, yet odd, prophecy.

24.text: The Human Torch must fight fire with fire when a lava man named Molto attacks him.

25.text: Home is where the HELL is! A friend of Daimon's mysteriously disappears along with their whole family, but when Daimon finally finds them, the demon Allatou is less than willing to give them up!

29.text: Shang-Chi, Master of Kung Fu has his goals set and will stop at nothing to achieve them in “Two Goals to Seek, One Path to Glory!”

30.text: Luke Cage finally gets the recognition he deserves; Power Man is on the front page!

32.text: When Spider-Man puts a stop to a robbery at the Guggenheim Museum, the perps tell him they were hired by a Kung Fu master named Shang-Chi. It's SUPERPOWERS versus MARTIAL ARTS in this epic battle royale!

33.text: Demmy Marston holds Shang-Chi responsible for the death of his girlfriend at the hands of Korain…and puts a price on his head! Add Marston to the list of folks who want the Master of Kung Fu dead!

36.text: Jack Russell is the Werewolf by Night, a young man trapped in a lycanthropic nightmare! The reign of terror continues when Jack battles a creature straight out of a horror novel- the Monster of Victor Frankenstein! The Brotherhood of Baal comes to a close.

37.text: Man-Thing restores harmony to a married couple after thwarting a demonic presence in their swamp.

38.text: The mutilated former actor now known as Atlas murders movie producer Simon Kolb in cold blood - and Jack Russell is taken in for the crime!

43.text: One of the first adventures of Deathlok the Demolisher! Deathlok, now a “Death Machine for Hire”, goes after his first victim. But what does Simon Ryker have in store for Deathlok after his first kill?

51.text: Matt Murdock investigates the disappearance of Professor Ted Sallis, and gains intel on the Floridian swamp creature known as the Man-Thing.

52.text: Harold Meachum wants Iron Fist dead, and he isn’t afraid to lay a few Kung Fu traps to get what he wants! Iron Fist goes after the man who placed a bounty on his head. Enter the Ninja, a mysterious hand-on-hand combatant who may prove an ally to Iron Fist!

53.text: Unable to defeat the Monster of Badoon by themselves, the Thing, Captain America, and Sharon Carter call upon the help of the Guardians of the Galaxy!

54.text: Doc Strange faces Death itself at the center of the Orb of Agamotto.

56.text: Namor vs. the SLIME-THING! What is this mysterious creature, and why does it have a vendetta against the Sub-Mariner?

57.text: Spider-Man sees Cat-Man with a briefcase and suspects he's up to something -- only for Daredevil to intervene!

68.text: Will Shang Chi still be the Master of Kung Fu after starring in the "Circle of Serpent's Blood”?

69.text: Shang-Chi's training is put to the ultimate test as he attempts to confront his father Fu Manchu and survive the assassins the man has sent to kill him.

70.text: Smalltime hood Demmy Marston wants to collect the reward on Shang-Chi's head and hires Korain the samurai, a former affiliate of Fu Manchu's to carry out the job!

71.text: PANTHER’S RAGE PART 6: T’Challa sets out for N’Jadaka to solve the mystery of Zatama’s murder.

77.text: Out of the frying pan and into…the mouths of hungry wolves? The Monster escapes Castle Frankenstein only to be bait for the savage wilderness. An icy hibernation begins.

78.text: El Tigre undergoes a strange mutation!

79.text: Man-Thing inadvertently causes distress to an elderly woman living deep in the swamps. Later, the swamp monster comes to the rescue of the woman's husband, embroiling himself in the couple's lives.

80.text: In the battle of Werewolves, who will emerge triumphant and free of the curse?

81.text: “Blood Bath”! Killraven and his crew can’t catch a moment’s rest -- they are now fighting for their lives in Michigan!

85.text: Doctor Strange enters the Orb of Agamotto, encountering trouble at every turn and bend.

88.text: Spider-Man and Brother Voodoo join forces after saving a woman from an attack by agents of Moondog the Malicious.

91.text: BOOM! A bright light flashes and the FF suddenly find themselves in a prehistoric world brought upon by a mysterious villain!
